LOLA: Location Overlap Analysis

LOLA is an R package providing functions for testing overlap of a set of genomic regions with public and custom databases.

Please see the R documentation for more details.

################################################################################
#HOW TO INSTALL
#install the development version directly from github with devtools

require(devtools)

#LOLA will rely on this public R package I wrote:
install_github("sheffien/simpleCache") # for a public repo

#for a private repo:
install_github("sheffien/LOLA", "YOUR_USERNAME", auth_token="YOUR PAT") #private
#Create your PAT (personal access token) here: https://github.com/settings/applications


#to install a local copy:
packageFolder = "~/Rncs/LOLA";
install.packages(packageFolder, repos=NULL)

################################################################################
#HOW TO RUN

library(LOLA)
?LOLA

Now take a look at examples.R for some examples. Vignettes forthcoming.


